         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Friday ¶  ¶ The very few men, left me in the Garden, dear Sir Redmond, are required to day to clear up a little for Queensbirthday &amp; Sunday. But so far as my ruinously reduced means will admit of it (...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">73.05.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Redmond Barry</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">UM312 1873/13, Registrar's correspondence, University of Melbourne Archives, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Friday</hi>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The very few men, left me in the Garden, dear Sir Redmond, are required to day to clear up a little for Queensbirthday &amp; Sunday. But so far as my ruinously reduced means will admit of it (we cannot even keep down the weeds) your application for plants again shall have my attention any early morning hour next week.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by R. Barry on 22 May: 'To the Registrar Please order Elliott [Alexander Elliott, head gardener] to make his arrangements to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>call<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on Dr Mueller on Tuesday next May 27. with a cart at 9 AM'. The date of Barry's note reveals, by implication, the date on which M's letter was written. '23rd May 1873'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has been written at the top of the letter in an unknown hand;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>this<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>be the date on which it was received,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Barry's annotation, at the University Registrar's Office.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I trust that this time my help after so many years will be for the benefit of my Department publicly acknowledged.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also M to R. Barry, 29 April 1873<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 73-04-29b).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regradfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
